I still think Jennifer was miscast, but given the fact they wanted Jennifer for it because of her popularity, they should have at least characterized her so she looked older, or they should have found a better way to justify her youth. But those are the only not so good things I saw; in general, it was a good film, an inspirational story for women (you have to be a woman to understand how the system sometimes doesn't cooperate with your dreams), and I stand happily corrected of my initial skepticism. Go watch this film, you will like it.
